    <section class="bio">
      <p>Thomas Van Roey is a PhD research fellow at the Department of Sociology at Ghent University. He previously obtained a Master of Arts degree in History at Ghent University (2014) and a Master of Arts degree in Nationalism Studies at Central European University (CEU Budapest, 2016).</p>
      <p>His research interests include multiculturalism, social identity and transnational migration. During his time at CEU in Budapest he worked as an intern at the Hungarian office of the International Organization for Migration (IOM), contributing to a project which aims to integrate persons under international protection in the local labour market.</p>
      <p>He participates in the multi-disciplinary project ‘Procedural fairness in local approaches to multicultural conflicts’, which includes researchers in the field of human rights law, social psychology and sociology. His PhD research focuses on the contextual variation in procedural fairness and its effects.</p>
